Question: Timothy, an HR director at an economic consulting firm, is reflecting on his delegation performance.
Which questions should he ask himself as part of his review of his own performance?
Instruction: Choose all options that best answer the question. 

Did I make helpful suggestions to assist the delegate?

Did I adequately prepare the tasks I delegated?

Did the delegation experience enhance my managerial abilities?

Did I follow up and support the delegate?

Did I provide enough instruction on what needed to be done?

Did the delegate adequately acknowledge my seniority and authority?
